articles.title: Kevin Spacey pleaded not guilty to sexual assault allegations
articles.description: Former "House of Cards" actor Kevin Spacey pleaded not guilty Monday to sexually assaulting an 18-year-old man in 2016. The case is ongoing and Spacey's next hearing is in March. Attorney Deborah Blum joins CBSN to discuss the case.

articles.title: Trump to address the nation ahead of border visit
articles.description: President Trump will address the nation Tuesday night, nearly three full weeks into a partial government shutdown. CBS News Washington correspondent Paula Reid joins CBSN's Elaine Quijano to discuss what would stop the stalled negotiations and ahead of Mr. Tr…

articles.title: Cyntoia Brown granted clemency after serving 15 years in prison
articles.description: A woman serving a life sentence for killing a man who bought her for sex has been granted clemency. Cyntoia Brown's case garnered national attention from criminal justice reform advocates. Mark Strassmann reports.

articles.title: Second suspect questioned in shooting death of 7-year-old Jazmine Barnes
articles.description: Investigators identified one suspect believed to be the getaway driver in a shooting that claimed the life of 7-year-old Jazmine Barnes. But they're questioning a second man who may be involved. Janet Shamlian reports.

articles.title: Stranger reunites 8-year-old boy recovering from surgery with his dog
articles.description: While visiting family in Utah, 8-year-old Perryn Miller found out he had a brain tumor. A stranger decided to bring him some comfort by driving Perryn's beloved dog Frank 2,300 miles to see him. Jim Axelrod has their story.

articles.title: 5G among highly-anticipated tech trends at CES 2019
articles.description: 5G is among the top tech trends expected to be talked about at the Consumer Electronics Show, which is being held this week in Las Vegas. CNET News executive editor Roger Cheng joins CBSN with the latest.

articles.title: Hillary Clinton, N.Y. Gov. Andrew Cuomo discuss abortion rights
articles.description: Former Secretary of State Hillary Clinton and New York Gov. Andrew Cuomo want to make abortion a constitutional right in New York state. The two made the announcement Monday at Barnard College in Manhattan. Cuomo called for an amendment last year.

articles.title: Government shutdown could impact airport wait times as TSA workers call out sick
articles.description: The partial government shutdown is starting to impact travelers. Wait times are up at many airports as some screeners call out sick, rather than work without pay. Kris Van Cleave reports.
